				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 27 Charm Song<a name="64812"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 29 04 10:01 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Target a creature and sing the song...  The creature becomes your buddy(for a few seconds).
<br />

<br />
If you don't have a Pet Window visible, press Alt-F1 and you'll get one.  You'll see your pet's health, buffs and some buttons to command him with.
<br />

<br />
You can also type in the commands or make hotkeys.  The commands always start with /pet.
<br />
/pet attack
<br />
/pet guard me
<br />
/pet back off
<br />
/pet guard here
<br />

<br />
Before long, your charm will wear off and he'll be really pissed at you.  Make sure you have Selo's or SoW up so that you dont' get eaten.  Since you're a bard, you can recast Charm on the run... this is a nice feature. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Invis will break your charm, and I've read that you can't charm MOBs that are a higher level than you are.
<br />

<br />
Good luck charming!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
