			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Leveling solo past 27<a name="65173"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 30 04 6:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At level 27, the problem with the first charm song is finishing off low on health former charms. You have 'Hard' aggro on them, there's not much another pet can do except stun, to keep them from chasing you untill they go into run, or die.
<br />

<br />
You can bellow them to death (I did).
<br />
   ie bellow/bellow/selos
<br />
   or for the brave, bellow/bellow/bellow/selos or snare
<br />

<br />
You can aggro kite if there are just two, ie, let a new charm beat on the old one chasing you or running, just make sure you drop a bellow on them to get full exp
<br />

<br />
You can wait until level thirty and you get a chant and chant/bellow/selos (or chant/bellow/bellow/snare) them down
<br />

<br />
(no selo's needed if you are using sow potions)
<br />

<br />
At 28 or 29 you can mini swarm the giants in GD around the EW zone. 2 or 3 in the swarm on a charm is about right. You can charm reds, but know that some berserkers are lvl 36 (or 37?)  and not charmable by the first song.
<br />

<br />
You can do the giants in IC including the guards at the span at this level as well, I believe. The area in front of the span to EW is a great swarming spot.
<br />

<br />
You can practice with mixed kites by adding a dog to the swarm.
<br />

<br />
If you just want to learn swarming, the sarnak fort in LOIO is a great place thats nearly deserted these days. The exp from swarming makes up for the crappy exp modifier in that zone.
<br />

<br />
That said, grouping almost any place with a GOOD group will rival the solo exp. If you want to learn swarm kiting, I think the first charm is an excellent way to do so, no mana limit is good and if get comfortable with it, you will often mem it with the 39 charm from 39-42 or so, just because its mana free and breaks quickly.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
