			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Leveling solo past 27<a name="65370"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 1 04 8:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>To swarm kite you charm a social mob and send him in to attack some of his friends.  If it goes well he'll be near death soon and you either break charm by going invis or charm breaks on it's own.  Either way you finish off you former pet with Bellows or fulfills then charm another critter and repeat.  I first swarmed cougars in IC,  that was with the 27 charm.  The main problem is that you will shortly get so much aggro from the other mobs that it does no good to sic your pet on them with the 27 song.  
<br />

<br />
It might be good to charm a giant in IC and have him kill wolves for you until his health is really low then finish him by fear kiting.  That always worked for me.  I'd use a SoW pot and equip a flute so as to never let charm drop.  I also gave the giants with no weapons Gnoll Hide Lariats.  After I killed the pet I'd retrive the lariats</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
